    "To see that R⇔win implies R-dense, suppose it is not the case that xR i y.",
    "Then by the right-to-left direction of R⇔win, there is a y ′ ⊑ y such that (i) ∀x ′ ⊑ x ∃x ′′ ⊑ x ′ ∀y ′′ ⊑ y ′, not x ′′ R i y ′′.",
    "Now we claim that for all y ′′ ⊑ y ′, it is not the case that xR i y ′′.",
    "For if xR i y ′′, then by the left-to-right direction of R⇔win, ∃x ′ ⊑ x ∀x ′′ ⊑ x ′ ∃y ′′′ ⊑ y ′′: x ′′ R i y ′′′, which with y ′′′ ⊑ y ′ contradicts (i).",
    "Thus, we have shown that if not xR i y, then ∃y ′ ⊑ y ∀y ′′ ⊑ y ′, not xR i y ′′, which is the contrapositive of R-dense.Next, we show that the stated conditions imply R⇔win."
